Eskom says its been in talks with President Cyril Ramaphosa to discuss solutions to the electricity crisis. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Eskom says its been in talks with President Cyril  Ramaphosa to discuss solutions to the electricity crisis. The utility's CEO, Andre de Ruyter, says he cannot disclose the exact contents of that meeting. WATCH | Eskom gives update on current system challenges South Africa is currently seesawing between Stage 4 and 6. "I was involved in two meetings with the president in the company of Minister Pravin Gordhan," De Ruyter said. "We fully briefed the president on the situation."